76561198007275020,Not Recommended,262120,15369152,"Posted: 14 April, 2015",all,ViccusV,"If you don't care about co-op, ignore my review and read someone elses.  My  review is aimed at people who really care about co-op.As a solo experience, Toy Soldiers is great.  However, If you're like me and thought about buying Toy Soldiers to play with friends, WAIT UNTIL THE MULTIPLAYER BUGS ARE FIXED.  I really can't stress that enough.  This game currently has desynchronization problems that make it unplayable for many people.  You may go several levels without the problem, but often your connection will sever and you'll both drop from the game.  As far as I can tell, retrying over and over will not ""luck"" your way past the bug.  Once you encounter it, its a wall you can't get past.  It's extremely frustrating and it's been an issue for months.  I realize this game is Early Access, but it deserves criticism as a standalone product if money is involved.  So consider yourself warned.Toy Soldiers is a great game on Xbox Live (good enough to buy it again on the PC) and I hope to one day see it fully operational on the PC, but until this game-breaking issue is resolved, I can't recommend it as a co-op experience."
