76561198048587276,Recommended,262120,15419641,"Posted: 17 April, 2015",all,รкг๏๏ℓ๏๏รε,"Toy Soldiers, the original game, is highly regarded as a standout among Xbox live arcade games and was the most sold Xbox live game of 2010! The porting of that game to PC was done surprisingly well. The end result was a great little RTS game based on kids toys for the PC that was very fun and enjoyable.http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=425501280Now, flash forward a few years, and you have this endeavor. An attempt to bring the entire Toy Soldiers universe into one game for the PC. Most of this game was never available on the PC before. In it's current form as of my writing this review, it still has some bugs and is missing some content. But based on past experiences with the previous port, and the fact that the game is around 90% complete, I can highly recommend this game. Just be aware.. it isn't 100% done yet.I dunno if it is the strategy part, the pace, or fps aspects.. but I love this game.http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=420103475And the whole toy story motif makes this one of the only games I would be willing to just sit and watch someone play. Watching toy planes bomb toy tanks while an old desk lamp from above lights the play surface.. it's art. So five stars and two thumbs up. If you like art, wrapped in fun, hidden inside a game...http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=425501632you'll like this game. And if you were a child who grew up in the seventies or eighties and played with toy soldiers.. make sure you have your heart medicine with you before you start playing.. cuz your heart may just burst with joy."
76561198098290580,Not Recommended,262120,31703588,Posted: 12 May,all,Legion2183,"I'm going to start out by saying I love Toy Soldiers. I played 75+ hours of the original's console version both on and off-line. It had a unique charm to it that felt like the developer's really took time in crafting a unique IP into a full fleshed out and realized game. If you have the chance to play the original I'd highly recommend it. It has its own unique sense of quirkiness and has a lot of twists on the Tower Defense Genre of games that make the level enjoyable to play over and over again. Part of the original's charm too was that the levels were challenging, but if you mastered those twists on the gameplay mechanics, and did well enough in the early rounds you could gradually build a fortress of defensive lines no one could penetrate.All of that makes what I am about to say that much harder. I can't recommend this game to nearly anyone in its current condition. The game has an excessive number of bugs for me which is odd considering that it runs fine with only a few frame rate drops sporadically. Units will fall through the map constantly for me to the point where some entire waves of enemies may as well not have spawned because they didn't even come into line of my forward gun positions. At the time of writing this I have beat every campaign and DLC in the game, except for the original Toy Soldier's main German campaign, and I have won literally every boss battle since the tutorial by the boss spawning, and then immediately dropping through the map only to despawn and be considered destroyed. Then a message pops up telling me congratulations your victory, though I never fired a shot. The game will also crash randomly on me during map loading or when a new wave spawns. Other times heat seeking missiles will just decide that they are not locked on and stop tracking the target half way through their flight. This is honestly astounding to me considering how much the original impressed me. I haven't been able to find anything on message boards saying that this is unique to a specific build or version, but I know that this is happening fairly frequently to others as well.Even when the game is not being a bug parade, the balancing is very messed up. There are some enemies that are capable of sustaining multiple direct hits from max upgraded artillery. This is fine on its own. In small batches it is a fun challenge to try and crush these bullet sponges as they drive up to your front line. The issue is when the developer has built a wave of these enemies that has 15 of these storming at you full speed, and the map only has two places to set artillery pieces it. Any other gun placement can barely touch these enemy types, and they will routinely break your lines causing you to leave the fun of building your base/ piloting a vehicle to turn around and mop up the remnants. In addition to this, the buildup of challenge is more of a cliff face than a traditional learning curve. Enemy waves start out with low armor and low numbers, but in the last five waves will ramp up to dozens of layered enemy types that are bullet sponges, some of whom can also just run over emplacements, destroying them in the process. The game at this point quickly becomes a test of how quickly can you spend money to get your gun emplacements back before the next wave, and this becomes tedious at best.In its current version I would go so far as to say the game is unplayable. To me that is a tremendous shame. The original brought me many hours of enjoyment with friends and by replaying the campaigns for their challenges to unlock various war memorabilia (another feature stripped from this version). This feels like a game that has lost any care that was originally placed into its IP. It comes across as a hollowed shell of a concept, filled with half-finished gameplay mechanics that was slapped together and never tested before release. Seeing as it has been out for a while not, and from what I can tell there have been little efforts to address these issues, I would say Signal Studios has given up on this project entirely. I emphatically do not recommend this game to fans of the genre and would recommend either trying to find a copy of the original for console or to look elsewhere if you are interested in something like this game, because what we were given can barely count as one."
