,Recommended,262120,13332598,"Posted: 12 December, 2014",all,The_Pastmaster,"Dispite some annoying CTD bugs and some balance issues that needs ironing out (Like that the British AA1 is superior to AA2 and 3) I very much recommend this game. It's fun and has a good bit of challenge. A good unit variety to shoot at and fun turrets to upgrade and use. Yes, you can man the turrets yourself (Except in the General game mode) and shoot at the enemy.You can also drive and pilot a variety of tanks, aircraft and choppers to help destroy the enemy. Vehicles run on batteries and will eventually run out unless charged up again. Don't worry about them getting blown up or the charge expiring. On most difficulties and modes they respawn and recharge after destruction so you can continue your rampage.The bosses are interesting though some are VERY annoying.One thing to mention is that you can play any of the four factions (Cold War US and Soviets, WW1 British and Germany) in any combinations in multiplayer. WW1 Germany against Cold War Soviets anyone?"
