,Recommended,262120,32954358,Posted: 28 June,all,mohomonkeyman,In the past I have found that tower defense games can be a grind and have been generally quite boring.. like a puzzle that you are only allowed to solve slowly.. but Toy Soldiers (and also Cubemen) have proven to me that this genre has more to offer. An intrinsic part of Toy Soldiers is the player's ability to take control of towers and units to give them more powerful effects. It adds a good amount of action to the game and in my opinion makes it well worth playing.
,Recommended,262120,17467246,"Posted: 9 August, 2015",all,Nightmare Duckie,"The first Toy Soldiers is one of my all time favorite games. The fact that this has the original Toy Soldiers and all of its DLC AND the second Toy Soldier and all of ITS DLC for $10 is amazing. At the time of writing this review I have 1.6 hours clocked in and have barley worked through the first campaign of the Cold War part, this pack gives you a lot of bang for your buck.I grew up playing countless tower defense flash games and this game is by far the best in the tower defense genre I have played. The selling-point mechanic that sets this game apart from other tower defense games is that you can take control of your various towers and vehicles on the map to fight the waves of enemies head on. While controlling a tower the game will give it bonus abilities, for example an AI mortar tower will fire one round then aim and fire again; when the play controls that same tower they can now fire three mortars in quick succession or take control of one fired shell, altering its course slightly and speed dramatically. However you can play the entire game without touching a vehicle or controlling a tower and play it as any other tower defense game, the vehicles and tower control will just give you that extra edge when things get tense and enemies slip through the lines.This game is beautifully themed and designed, all the soldiers, vehicles, towers, and environments are in the style of an old war diorama model kit. The vehicles are all wind up, the soldiers are all display figures, the towers are all little glued together models, and the maps all take place in open model terrain cases, complete with painted cardboard sky and cloud borders on maps that give you a plane.One of my favorite parts of the game is the ability to pause it at any time and enter ""Tilt-Shift mode"" which brings the depth of field and focal point really close up and drops the camera to near the ground so you can take some awesome screenshots, check out my Toy Soldiers screenshots on my profile for some examples.The maps offer a fair bit of challenge to them but you can always make it harder by playing on a harder difficultly. There are other gamemodes like Survival and with this complete pack there's even multiplayer, but I haven't tried that out yet.A final note is that the music and sound design is superb, Signal has really made a great game, I consider this my 'perfect game' for this genre."
