76561198102317602,Recommended,262120,28796717,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,JJST,"This is my first review so please muddle through it with we! :)  I enjoy the game.  I played the original Toy Soldiers on Xbox 360 as well as Cold War.  I remember back in the day I was enchanted by the fun of the cartoony men and wind-em-up tanks.  The little pop of a toy as I nailed it at 100 meters with my sniper tower.  The tension of that one enemy troop nearly making it into my beloved toybox.  I poured a lot of time into the 360 version.  It was fun.Now on my PC rig I have that same pleasure!  The game is still fun.  For me the biggest pro in favor of this game: the shear time pleasing experience.  It is a basic tower defence with good character.  The controls are fluid and easy to use(with a controller).  The environment is somewhat destructible and generally nice to fly around.  The base setup is well thought out and variously flavored.However, this game does suffer from a few technical errors.  The frame rate is generally good but can be susceptible to some drops.  A few bugs here and there, but nothing to really turn me off to the game.To round up, the game is fun.  It has a nice feel even though it can be a bit buggy.  So, if you can not stand a few bugs, this title is not for you.  But, if you are looking for a good title that is a bunch of fun, certainly pick this one up on sale. Cheers!"
