,Recommended,262120,24943830,"Posted: 15 August, 2016",all,"Oborawatabinost, The Fiscal Mage","This is one of my favorite game series out there. After finding the origional Toy solider back on the Xbox marketplace, I was immediately taken in by the perfect balance between tower defense, RTS, and a bit of some 3rd person shooting elements. The WWI theme was well executed and the ""fiction"" aspects, such as the rare tanks and bosses, only further developed the theme.The series continues by extending into the Cold War. Just like before, the mixture of gameplay styles blend well together and the theme is noticeable. However, despite the ""raw fun"" gameplay; there are some issues. The user interface isn't as intuitive as before; as switching/selecting units can be difficult at times, due to some wonky hit boxes and camera angles. There are also their far share of bugs, ranging from hilarious to game breaking. On one hand, the game froze but was quick to recover to a good auto-save system; on the other hand, two bosses fell threw the stage and were killed near immediately. This left me more disappointed than anything else, as I really do enjoy the creative boss fights.Overall, the polish isn't there but it is clear that the dev team made an effort to create a fun/unique experience that builds of the previous game."
